@page "/changelog"

<PageTitle>Changelog — Crittr</PageTitle>

<div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto py-4">

    <div class="mb-8">
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white tracking-tight">What's new</h1>
        <p class="mt-1 text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm">Release notes and updates for Crittr.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- v1.3.0 -->
    <div class="relative pl-6 border-l-2 border-green-200 dark:border-green-800 mb-12">
        <div class="absolute -left-2.5 top-0 w-4 h-4 rounded-full bg-green-600 border-2 border-white dark:border-gray-950"></div>

        <div class="mb-1 flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-green-600 dark:text-green-400">Latest</span>
            <span class="text-xs text-slate-400">April 2026</span>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4">v1.3.0 — Cohabitation Intelligence &amp; Species-Specific Feeding</h2>

        <div class="space-y-6 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">

            <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Gender-aware cohabitation rules</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                    <li>Every species now has a <strong>GenderPairingRule</strong> — 25 species updated with male-male conflict data</li>
                    <li>Hard blocks for lethal pairings: two male Leopard Geckos, Canaries, African Cichlids, and more will be blocked with a specific fatal-conflict message</li>
                    <li>Soft warnings for serious-but-not-always-lethal pairings: Cockatiels, tortoises, cichlids, rabbits</li>
                    <li>Unknown sex triggers a warning: "if both are male, these may fight"</li>
                    <li>Conflict messages include the resident's pet name, species, and species-specific behavioral note (e.g. "Will bully and stress cage mates")</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Client-side cohabitation checks</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                    <li><code class="text-xs bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-800 px-1 rounded">CohabitationCatalog</code> in the shared library — all 110+ species profiles compiled into the browser bundle</li>
                    <li>All cohabitation checks on the dashboard and critter detail page run entirely client-side — zero server round-trips, instant response</li>
                    <li>Critter detail dropdown is now filtered at load time: enclosures where the incoming critter can't cohabit are hidden before the user even sees them</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Dashboard drag visual system</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                    <li>Three-state drag feedback: green ring (compatible), orange ring (cohabitation concern), dimmed/greyed (wrong enclosure type)</li>
                    <li>Critter cards in the homeless panel glow orange when they have a cohabitation conflict with the currently-viewed enclosure</li>
                    <li>Hover message on enclosure shows all conflicts with pet names and species-specific notes</li>
                    <li>Type-incompatible enclosures show a red "Wrong enclosure type" message on hover — no more silent greying</li>
                    <li>Cohabitation concern message stays visible for 3 seconds after drop, then fades out smoothly — unified hover and post-drop message</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Species-specific feeding form</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                    <li>Feeding form adapts based on the critter's species type</li>
                    <li><strong>Reptiles, amphibians, invertebrates:</strong> quick-count buttons [1][2][3][4][5] + stepper + "Ate it / Refused" toggle</li>
                    <li><strong>Fish:</strong> portion selector (Pinch / Small / Medium / Large) replaces numeric quantity</li>
                    <li><strong>Birds:</strong> serving-based logging, no consumed toggle</li>
                    <li>Date and time captured together — feedings now log the hour, not just the day</li>
                    <li>New <code class="text-xs bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-800 px-1 rounded">FeedingUnit</code> field on every feeding record (Items / Portion / Pinch / Serving / Grams)</li>
                    <li>Feeding history displays unit-aware labels: "4× Crickets", "Large portion · Betta Pellets", "Serving · Pellets"</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">UX &amp; guide improvements</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                    <li>"How It Works" guide page expanded with cohabitation rule explanations, color-coded rule cards, and species examples</li>
                    <li>Feeding date field replaced with datetime picker — Now shortcut + clock icon for custom time</li>
                    <li>Homeless critter sidebar stacks below carousel on all viewports; floats left at 2xl+ without compressing the carousel</li>
                    <li>Custom enclosure type disabled as "Coming Soon" in the creation wizard</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- v1.2.0 -->
    <div class="relative pl-6 border-l-2 border-green-200 dark:border-green-800 mb-12">
        <div class="absolute -left-2.5 top-0 w-4 h-4 rounded-full bg-slate-300 dark:bg-slate-600 border-2 border-white dark:border-gray-950"></div>

        <div class="mb-1 flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="text-xs text-slate-400">April 2026</span>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4">v1.2.0 — Species Intelligence &amp; Cohabitation</h2>

        <div class="space-y-6 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">

            <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Per-species enclosure compatibility</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                    <li>Enclosure wizard now filters by the specific species, not just the broad category — Ball Python gets Terrarium only; Red-eared Slider gets Tank + Aquarium</li>
                    <li>Critter detail page label ("needs a terrarium") is generated live from the actual compatible type list, not a hardcoded string</li>
                    <li>Fallback to species-type-level compatibility when species isn't in the catalog</li>
                    <li>New endpoint: <code class="text-xs bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-800 px-1 rounded">GET /api/species/info?name=</code></li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Cohabitation rules</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                    <li>Every species in the catalog now has a social profile: Solo Only, Pairs OK, Groups OK, or Community</li>
                    <li>Assigning a critter to a non-empty enclosure triggers a compatibility check before confirming</li>
                    <li>Hard blocks (e.g. any critter into a Bearded Dragon's enclosure) prevent assignment entirely</li>
                    <li>Soft warnings (e.g. different animal types) show an "Assign anyway" option</li>
                    <li>New endpoint: <code class="text-xs bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-800 px-1 rounded">GET /api/enclosure/{"{id}"}/cohabitation?critterId=</code></li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">CritterCondition health scoring</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                    <li>Health badges computed from feeding cadence, shedding history, and pending tasks: Thriving / Good / Fair / Needs Attention / Critical</li>
                    <li>Badges visible on dashboard enclosure cards and critter detail pages</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Enclosure type fixes</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                    <li>Removed Free-Roam Room from Bird and Reptile compatibility — it belongs to mammals only (ferrets, rabbits)</li>
                    <li>Custom / Other enclosure type is now disabled in the creation wizard, shown as Coming Soon</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">UI improvements</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                    <li>Feeding form: date and quantity now share a row instead of each taking a full-width line</li>
                    <li>New "How It Works" guide page explaining cohabitation rules, species compatibility, and health scoring — accessible via the <svg class="inline w-3.5 h-3.5 mb-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 16v-4M12 8h.01"/></svg> icon in the nav</li>
                    <li>Enclosure type cards in the creation wizard now show substrate and size presets seeded to the type</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- v1.1.0 -->
    <div class="relative pl-6 border-l-2 border-green-200 dark:border-green-800 mb-12">
        <div class="absolute -left-2.5 top-0 w-4 h-4 rounded-full bg-slate-300 dark:bg-slate-600 border-2 border-white dark:border-gray-950"></div>

        <div class="mb-1 flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="text-xs text-slate-400">April 2026</span>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4">v1.1.0 — Enclosure Type System</h2>

        <div class="space-y-6 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">

            <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Enclosure creation wizard</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                    <li>New 3-step modal: pick a type → set up the environment → name it</li>
                    <li>12 enclosure types with emoji, description, and smart field presets per type</li>
                    <li>Aquarium/Tank hides humidity and shows Aquarium Heater instead of Heating Element</li>
                    <li>Free-Roam Room shows room dimensions with optional 0 values</li>
                    <li>Blank name auto-fills from the selected type (e.g. "My Aquarium")</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Enclosure type theming</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                    <li>Dashboard canvas background and border colour match the enclosure type</li>
                    <li>Decorative SVG overlays: bubbles for aquatic, foliage for terrariums, bars for cages</li>
                    <li>Enclosure detail page hero section uses per-type gradient and overlay</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Species ↔ enclosure compatibility</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                    <li>Full compatibility matrix: which species types belong in which enclosure types</li>
                    <li>Critter wizard filters enclosure list and species options by compatibility</li>
                    <li>Server endpoint <code class="text-xs bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-800 px-1 rounded">GET /api/enclosure/dto/compatible?speciesType=</code> returns only compatible enclosures</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Bug fixes</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                    <li>Fixed: enclosure type was not saved to the database — all enclosures were stored as Terrarium regardless of what was selected</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- v1.0.0 -->
    <div class="relative pl-6 border-l-2 border-green-200 dark:border-green-800">
        <div class="absolute -left-2.5 top-0 w-4 h-4 rounded-full bg-slate-300 dark:bg-slate-600 border-2 border-white dark:border-gray-950"></div>

        <div class="mb-1 flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="text-xs text-slate-400">March 2025</span>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4">v1.0.0 — Initial Release</h2>

        <div class="space-y-6 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">

            <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Enclosures</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                    <li>Create and manage enclosures with type, dimensions, substrate, temperature and humidity targets</li>
                    <li>UVB lighting and heating element flags</li>
                    <li>Carousel view on the dashboard with swipe support on mobile</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Critters</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                    <li>Add critters with species search powered by iNaturalist</li>
                    <li>Track name, sex, date of birth, date acquired, weight, and morph / notes</li>
                    <li>Assign critters to enclosures from the dashboard</li>
                    <li>Critter icons rendered inside the enclosure canvas</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Feeding log</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                    <li>Log feedings with food item, item type, quantity, consumption status, and notes</li>
                    <li>Track last feeding date per critter; full feeding history grouped by month</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Health &amp; measurements</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                    <li>Weight and length measurement history</li>
                    <li>Shedding records</li>
                    <li>Behavior log</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Platform</h3>
                <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                    <li>Blazor WebAssembly progressive web app</li>
                    <li>JWT authentication with secure token storage</li>
                    <li>Works on desktop and mobile browsers</li>
                    <li>MAUI Blazor Hybrid target (in progress)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>

</div>
